# System status page

The app has a **login-only** health page at **`/status`** (`app/(dashboard)/status/page.tsx`).

## When to update

After **systematic** project changes, update in the same PR/commit:

1. **`lib/systemStatusManifest.ts`** — phases, migrations list, required env vars, bump `manifestVersion`
2. **`lib/systemHealthCheck.ts`** — new table probes or env checks when schema/infra changes
3. **Login landing** — default post-auth path is `/` (Home); `/status` is in the nav for health checks

Trigger examples: new migration, new major route/page, new required env var, shipped/planned phase, auth or RLS change.

## Do not

- Expose secret values on `/status` (boolean/set-only for env)
- Add `/status` to public routes in `middleware.ts`
- Skip manifest update when adding a migration users must run

## Quick checklist

- [ ] Phase row added or status changed in manifest
- [ ] Migration row added if new `supabase/migrations/*.sql`
- [ ] Health probe for new tables if applicable
- [ ] `manifestVersion` date bumped
